sub_title: EMCC Accredited Coach & Mentor at Practitioner Level
summary:
Extensive experience in working and leading multinational and multicultural teams. Raised in Türkiye, completed my education in Business Economics in the Netherlands, worked as a teacher in a multicultural high school, then subsequently established my international business and served at various leadership positions in a leading global NGO. 

Strong interest in the area of learning and development. Supported young professionals, start-ups and entrepreneurs thru coaching, mentoring and leadership trainings. 

An entrepreneur with a fulfilling international business experience. After moving to Türkiye established the Istanbul franchise of AngloInfo.com (a leading worldwide online marketing & advertising platform) and lately acted as the managing director and the owner of a niche corporate executive training company in Istanbul. After moving to The Netherlands again, worked at Kroes Immigration Lawyers Law Firm as Head of Türkiye desk. 

Driven, result oriented, well rounded, outspoken, motivating, reliable and hard worker team player with strong experience in leadership, management, online marketing & advertising, effective governance, project management, coaching&mentoring and working in a multicultural work environment.
